The paper deals with sublinear-time algorithms for image analysis, which is a topic closely related to computer vision (cs.CV). The algorithms also involve sampling and testing properties of the image, which falls under the categories of data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also mentions the use of PAC learning, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper involves algorithms for convexity and connectedness, which are topics in computational geometry (cs.CG).
